name: The Friendly Spot Ice House

name: Brooklyn Park City Hall

name: Guildhall

name: Dollar Tree

name: Shear Thairapy

name: University of West of England Z block

name: Korner Lounge

name: Kingston Ten Pin

name: MSU Federal Credit Union

comment: This is a financial institution so the restrooms are meant for members, but it is easy to join and way better than a bank. So if you live or work in the area, this is a progressive welcoming place.

name: Marigold and Honey Cafe
directions: Located inside the Botanical Garden
comment: Admission or membership required

name: Kent District Library - Wyoming Branch

comment: Ask any staff member and they will point you in the right direction.

name: Prairie Care
directions: Through first door on the right when you walk in the main entrance, restrooms located just to the left of the front desk
comment: is a psychiatric office so you’d have to act like you belong there or ask the receptionist

name: Old Courthouse Museum
directions:
1st floor - down the hallway from the front desk
2nd floor - located at the end of the hallway next to the staff only doors
comment: This is a free public museum. The front desk can also point you in the direction of the bathrooms as well.

name: Booster Juice
directions: Past the order desk, down the hallway second door on the on the left.
comment: You do have to be a paying customer, so act like you’re going to order and just say “oh I have to use the washroom”

name: Stormcrow Manor
directions: Two options. One is down a single flight of steep stairs to the basement level, where there are about ten fully enclosed single stalls and a shared sink space. The other is up a gentle flight of stairs with a thick hand rail to the second floor, where there are two single stalls with sinks inside the stalls.
comment: This is a restaurant and you will likely be asked to purchase something before you can use the washroom. Staff are explicitly trained on being welcoming to all genders and the establishment employs several openly GNC people. The signage for the bathrooms does have the cheeky "whatever, just wash your hands" with pictures of nonhuman creatures.

name: Tanker Jetty Public Toilets
directions: Located right by the Tanker Jetty carpark.
comment: Open Monday’s, Tuesday’s, Wednesday’s and Friday’s from 8am to 6pm. Open Thursday’s 8am to 9pm. Saturday’s open 8am to 5pm. Closed Sundays.

name: Lentil as Anything, Thornbury
directions: In the back of the building, straight down the hall.
comment: It's a very lovely and welcoming place to everyone. Try some pay-as-you-feel vegan food while you're there!

name: D Pet Hotel
directions: Park behind the building. Bathroom is right inside the door to the right.
comment: Everyone is great there. Just say you need the restroom.

name: O Covil
directions: in the back of the tavern on the left side

name: 801 Mt Vernon Pl NW, Washington, DC 20001, USA
comment: DC Convention Center

name: Fanshawe Conservation Area Day Use
directions: Day Use Area of Park.  Between Pioneer Village and Safety Village
comment: Pay to get into park.  Seasonal

name: East Hill Lift Upper Station
directions: Round the right of the station.
comment: Public toilet run by council. No requirement to use the lift.

name: Zuckerbäckerei
directions: When you go through the front door, you enter a small hallway. The gender neutral single stall toilet is right from the door through which you enter the café.
comment:
Mind that this is a café and you might ask for permission to use the toilet first.

There are two or three small steps up to the front door, so it's not directly accessible. I'm not sure if it's accessible if you enter over the terrasse.

name: Woods Coffee
directions: In the back behind the stairs.
comment: No code required and they wouldn't know if you bought something or not.

name: El recreo de Adan
directions: Bathroom is upstairs. Really friendly people LGBTQIA friendly
comment: You have to be a paying cs. So I would advise actually enjoying the place

name: Dunedin
directions: Directions are inside the restaurant, to the right hand side on the way to the back

name: Columbia Gorge Community College - Hood River Campus
comment: Columbia Gorge Community College is dedicated to protecting our LGBT members and providing a safe space for them.

name: Big Time Fun Center
directions: Past the other two bathrooms. Door has a code and you need to ask for it at the desk
comment: My trans kid marched herself up to the owner and said, "I'm trans and you need to have a gender neutral bathroom!" He said, "we do!" and then gave us a bunch of free passes for her bravery.

name: Generations Pizzaria
directions: In the back of the restaurant. The nice servers will lead you there.

name: Angles
comment: Nightclub,  does have entry fee

name: VCA Bering Sea

name: Bluegrass Community & Technical College

name: Trinity Lutheran Church
comment: I spoke with someone who works there and she said she has always assumed it's a safe place. My mom worked here for years and also believes it would be a safe place for anyone trans and non-binary.

name: Krua Thai
directions: In far back of restaurant
